cs.HCI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper investigates how end-users conceptualize and engage in machine teaching, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and machine learning (LG) techniques applied to computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (CL) tasks. The study also explores users' misconceptions and reflections on their teaching strategies, which can inform the development of more effective and user-friendly teachable interfaces (CY).
